ol.li: Source: Syscall RDI holds pointer to tracee memory string.
Peek: PTRACE_PEEKDATA reads exactly one machine word (8 bytes).
Loop: Iterate words, casting to char* to search for \0.
Boundary: Since path can cross page boundaries, tracer handles address increments.
Stop: Terminate loop immediately when 0x00 is detected in the current word.

div.p: c char path[PATH_MAX]; // Result // Buffer content after copy: "/etc/passwd\0"
